"If you are not with us you are against us. To be against us is to be your doom as death will be your only salvation"</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=FAEBD7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub73.ezboard.com/ucoldsunsz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ColdsunSZ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>poon</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/15/01 12:55:01 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Mage VS Wiz</span><hr size=1> That's PVE, pvp wise mages are very strong against classes that can't root or snare (basically melee).<br>
<br>
If a mage with pet jumps a wizard the wizard will probably lose unless he does some intelligent shadowstep/yondering and then comes back to jump the mage.<br>
<br>
The wizard must root the pet to have any chance, if you try to cast through the pet hitting you, the wizard will die.<br>
<br>
On plain 1 on 1 nuking the wizard will kill the mage easy, but casters have little hp so if the mage gets a good jump on the wiz he may be able to outnuke the wizard enough to kill him first.<br>
<br>
Wizard spells PVP are resisted very well if the target has high resistance in that category.  Wizard lure spells are king, and once you get 56 ice lure that spell is seriously deadly to any caster, even with high cold resist.  Lures do have a slower cast time for their damage amount though.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#DEB887><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub73.ezboard.com/uagrul.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Agrul</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Tavern Regular</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/15/01 1:03:20 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Mage VS Wiz</span><hr size=1> Mage vs. Wizard, Upper Level PvP, My Take On It:<br>
<br>
It's all about dispelling Immobilizes off your pet, having the resists to ignore Draughts, and getting your pet back in their face in time to interrupt Lures.<br>
<br>
How to deal with Rains:  When you recognize that a Rain spell is being cast (and they tend to have very unique casting graphics, so it isn't that hard), run up next to them and let the Rain hit both of you.  They lose mana, and you both lose health, depending on your sv WhateverSortOfRainSpellItWas.<br>
<br>
How to deal with Shock of Lightning:  Practice tapping forward as it hits you to lessen the need to channel through the knockback effect.  Shove yourself into a corner so as to negate the knockback effect.  Use fast-casting spells to slip inbetween the Shock of Lightnings.<br>
<br>
Make use of Bolts:  As the Wizard is dealing with your pet, it's always fun to stand oor. of their casting range and just pummel them with Scars.  The damage isn't that bad, and the casting range is phenomonal.<br>
<br>
Agrul <p></center>
